00:00:06.030 --> 00:00:07.590
SRIDHAR RAMASWAMY: Hello.

00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:09.560
Welcome, everybody.

00:00:09.560 --> 00:00:11.620
It's always fun to have
mid-afternoon sessions

00:00:11.620 --> 00:00:12.563
in a hot tent.

00:00:15.810 --> 00:00:17.090
My name is Sridhar Ramaswamy.

00:00:17.090 --> 00:00:20.820
I lead the Ads and
Commerce teams at Google.

00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:23.390
And here with me is
Pali Bhat, the product

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:25.680
lead for Payments at Google.

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:28.620
And we're really
excited to be talking

00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:33.800
to you about all the latest
and greatest in Android Pay.

00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:38.730
I want to start by addressing
the elephant in the room.

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:43.080
There are tons of pays
that are out there.

00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:47.660
And all of you want to
know, who's winning?

00:00:47.660 --> 00:00:50.520
Is there a winner?

00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:54.370
But the sad answer
is, no, not really.

00:00:54.370 --> 00:00:57.240
There is no winner.

00:00:57.240 --> 00:01:01.930
Legacy payment methods like
the credit card and cash

00:01:01.930 --> 00:01:04.280
are still the dominant
payment methods

00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:06.120
that are being used out there.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:08.360
Even the most avid
technology enthusiasts

00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:13.530
among us is
hesitant, are scared,

00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:17.640
to leave our credit
cards and cash behind.

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:22.380
And the natural question
is, what's holding us back?

00:01:22.380 --> 00:01:24.160
We thought a lot about this.

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:27.990
And we think there are
three big reasons for this.

00:01:30.610 --> 00:01:33.540
The first of course,
is a big one--

00:01:33.540 --> 00:01:36.952
is that all the mobile payment
methods are kind of limited.

00:01:39.550 --> 00:01:42.350
Some work for the physical
contactless terminals.

00:01:42.350 --> 00:01:44.270
Some work with all terminals.

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:48.841
You know, sometimes it works
in-app but not in-- not

00:01:48.841 --> 00:01:49.590
on the mobile web.

00:01:49.590 --> 00:01:52.760
And we're going to
talk a lot about that.

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:56.230
It's the unpredictability of
whether your mobile payment

00:01:56.230 --> 00:01:59.260
method is going to work,
that makes you want to say,

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:03.920
no, I can't rely on
it 100% of the time.

00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:06.330
We think the second
big reason is

00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:10.240
that a lot of the payment
schemes that are out there

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:11.560
are kind of uncompelling.

00:02:11.560 --> 00:02:15.160
You're talking about an
activity that all of us

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:16.800
do many times a
week, that we have

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:20.920
done the same way
for many, many years.

00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:23.530
And so if you're going
to go ask humanity

00:02:23.530 --> 00:02:26.630
to change the way that they
think about payments, what's

00:02:26.630 --> 00:02:27.980
the value-add?

00:02:27.980 --> 00:02:29.190
They're kind of uncompelling.

00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:32.910
And this is something we really
do want to address as well.

00:02:32.910 --> 00:02:35.990
And we actually think that
the uncompelling nature

00:02:35.990 --> 00:02:39.530
of the payment solution comes
about because most payment

00:02:39.530 --> 00:02:41.270
solutions are kind of closed.

00:02:41.270 --> 00:02:47.090
They have a few key pieces of
functionality, and that's it.

00:02:47.090 --> 00:02:49.340
What makes our
smartphones great,

00:02:49.340 --> 00:02:53.260
whether it's Android or iOS, is
not just the operating system.

00:02:53.260 --> 00:02:58.177
We like aspects of our phones
that come directly from Google.

00:02:58.177 --> 00:03:00.260
But the fact of the matter
is what we really love,

00:03:00.260 --> 00:03:02.530
are our apps.

00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:05.080
It's a great functionality
that comes on.

00:03:05.080 --> 00:03:07.210
Is that animation
the developers like

00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:12.310
you have provided on
the core platform.

00:03:12.310 --> 00:03:16.080
There is no comparable
thing that's

00:03:16.080 --> 00:03:18.210
going on in mobile payments.

00:03:18.210 --> 00:03:20.690
We think that's kind
of a big blocker.

00:03:20.690 --> 00:03:23.810
So what do we want to do?

00:03:23.810 --> 00:03:27.115
Today we're going to be talking
to you about all the things

00:03:27.115 --> 00:03:30.250
that we at Android
Pay and Google

00:03:30.250 --> 00:03:38.300
are doing to make mobile
payments better for merchants

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:42.490
and retailers, for
financial institutions,

00:03:42.490 --> 00:03:48.060
but most of all for
consumers, like you and me.

00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:50.060
We think payments should
work everywhere they're

00:03:50.060 --> 00:03:50.880
expected to work.

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:55.061
They should work in a
simple and secure way.

00:03:55.061 --> 00:03:56.810
And we think mobile
payments would be more

00:03:56.810 --> 00:04:01.700
